OL,7,FIn December last year, an Old Bailey
OL,8,Fjury deliberated for two hours before
OL,9,Ffinding Jacques, of Minard Road,
OL,10,FLewisham, south-east London, guilty of
OL,11,Ffour counts of murder.
OL,13,FThe judge was invited by the
OL,14,Fprosecution to consider whether the
OL,15,F"exceptional nature" of the multiple
OL,16,Fkillings warranted a whole life
OL,17,Fsentence.
